thnic diversity, increased segregation, exclusive growth of minority groups through immigration and a national identity crisis. The contributions, all from experts in the field based at or affiliated to the Centre on Dynamics of Ethnicity, highlight persistent inequalities in access to housing, employment, education and good health faced by some ethnic groups. The book will be a valuable resource for policy makers and researchers in national and local government, community groups, academics, students, and will act as an authoritative text to cite in reports, dissertations and funding applications.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aByrne, Bridget, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBécares, Laia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCatney, Gemma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClark, Ken, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinney, Nissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarries, Bethan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJivraj, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJivraj, Stephen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKapadia, Dharmi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhan, Omar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLymperopoulou, Kitty, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNazroo, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParameshwaran, Meenakshi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimpson, Ludi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular